2. Law and Ratio

The earliest codes, from Hammurabi to Moses, were numeric: â€œseven years,â€ â€œtenfold restitution,â€ â€œforty days.â€  Law was proportion long before it was bureaucracy.  When ratio became forgotten and literalism replaced symbolism, justice lost its music.

To restore harmonic jurisprudence is to view law as calibration.  Punishment becomes re-tuning; rehabilitation becomes re-entry into resonance.  The purpose of judgment is not to condemn dissonance but to reintegrate it into the greater theme.

