10. Toward Planetary Unity

The Harmonic Civilization culminates in recognition that humanity is a single chord within a cosmic composition.  National borders, racial divisions, and religious antagonisms are temporary modulations in a larger symphony.  As communication networks and global awareness expand, dissonance gives way to emergent consonance â€” the slow tuning of species consciousness.

Unity does not mean uniformity.  In harmony, each voice retains timbre while contributing to whole.  Diversity is not obstacle but richness of overtone.  When societies understand this musically, war becomes obsolete â€” the cacophony that no longer pleases the ear of evolution.


